properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 18 at 11:38AM CST until January 18 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Sioux Falls SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blowing snow. Winds gusting as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...Brule and Charles Mix Counties.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility. The cold wind chills as low as 25 below zero could
cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST THIS EVENING... ...BLIZZARD WARNING IS CANCELLED
